{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-article-template-js","path":"/the-problem-with-weight-loss","result":{"data":{"BlogPostByPath":{"html":"<h2 id=\"when-did-we-stop-trusting-ourselves\" style=\"position:relative;\">When did we stop trusting ourselves?<a href=\"#when-did-we-stop-trusting-ourselves\" aria-label=\"when did we stop trusting ourselves permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>An app that counts calories and macros cannot tell us if we have had enough to eat.  It does not know what the body needs to meet the demands of the day.  It does not know how we feel.  By following something external, we give away our power and ignore our bodies and our intuition.</p>\n<p>Somewhere, we stopped asking ourselves how we feel.  Are you hungry?  Then you should eat.  It is very simple, but there is a lot of cultural programming against this.  We are told that foods are “good” or “bad”, yet food has no moral value.  We are overwhelmed with messaging that values thinness over how we feel.  Why?  Because it preys on our fears and produces huge profits.  We have been convinced that thin equals healthy.  But what is health?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5ed7ed55178412f9dad6700591bd2a91/17827/determinants_of_health.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 700px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Determinants of health by @holisticallygrace\"\n        title=\"Determinants of health by @holisticallygrace on Instagram\"\n        src=\"/static/5ed7ed55178412f9dad6700591bd2a91/046a4/determinants_of_health.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5ed7ed55178412f9dad6700591bd2a91/843e4/determinants_of_health.jpg 175w,\n/static/5ed7ed55178412f9dad6700591bd2a91/72334/determinants_of_health.jpg 350w,\n/static/5ed7ed55178412f9dad6700591bd2a91/046a4/determinants_of_health.jpg 700w,\n/static/5ed7ed55178412f9dad6700591bd2a91/eea25/determinants_of_health.jpg 1050w,\n/static/5ed7ed55178412f9dad6700591bd2a91/17827/determinants_of_health.jpg 1080w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/B5LOCnaAqID/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Source: Maria Sosa, MS, MFT, Therapist on Instagram</a></p>\n<p>As we can see by the wonderful illustration, health is multifaceted and cannot be reduced to “thinness”. </p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 id=\"selling-a-scam\" style=\"position:relative;\">Selling a scam<a href=\"#selling-a-scam\" aria-label=\"selling a scam permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>Dieting leads to disordered eating.  Following rules or restrictions outside of what our body is telling us creates an unhealthy relationship based on the fear of being fat (which plays into the cultural bias that fat is less valued).  Poor body image leading to restriction, restriction leads to feeling deprived, which leads to binging, which then cause bad feelings and poor body image.  It’s a violent cycle that leads many to disordered eating or to eating disorders.  </p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/710829646cdc7467fc4203dc66cc224f/17827/the-dieting-paradox.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 700px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"The Dieting Paradox by @zaonutrition\"\n        title=\"The Dieting Paradox by @zaonutrition on Instagram\"\n        src=\"/static/710829646cdc7467fc4203dc66cc224f/046a4/the-dieting-paradox.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/710829646cdc7467fc4203dc66cc224f/843e4/the-dieting-paradox.jpg 175w,\n/static/710829646cdc7467fc4203dc66cc224f/72334/the-dieting-paradox.jpg 350w,\n/static/710829646cdc7467fc4203dc66cc224f/046a4/the-dieting-paradox.jpg 700w,\n/static/710829646cdc7467fc4203dc66cc224f/eea25/the-dieting-paradox.jpg 1050w,\n/static/710829646cdc7467fc4203dc66cc224f/17827/the-dieting-paradox.jpg 1080w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/B6vaULylXmd/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Source: Grace Rockwell | Nutritionist</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Living your life in fear of something that may or may not be realistic is to not an intention that I would recommend.</p>\n<p>The idea of a before and after reinforces the withholding of self-love.  I will love myself/be happy when <strong>____</strong>.  It teaches us that we are not enough or worthy <em>right now</em>.  This is incredibly problematic and something that can be internalized far too easily.  It can take years to deprogram this cultural message.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 id=\"what-you-can-control\" style=\"position:relative;\">What you can control<a href=\"#what-you-can-control\" aria-label=\"what you can control permalink\" class=\"anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Do the hard internal work towards self-respect, self-acceptance and self-love</li>\n<li>Be present with your body and listen to it’s cues</li>\n<li>Learn about Intuitive Eating <a href=\"https://www.intuitiveeating.org/10-principles-of-intuitive-eating/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">10 Principles of Intuitive Eating | Intuitive Eating</a> </li>\n<li>Learn about Health at Every Size (HAES) <a href=\"https://isabelfoxenduke.com/health-at-every-size-haes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Health At Every Size (HAES): A Guide for Binge Eating Recovery - Isabel Foxen Duke</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>It is a long journey away from what you have heard your whole life.  Thin is not better.  Listening to your own body is better.  Missteps and mistakes will be made.  Be gentle with yourself.  Even as you make progress, it is natural to observe yourself slipping back on old ways of thinking.  Stay present with yourself and listen to your body.  The body is a miracle that does so many things we don’t even know about to keep us alive.  Trust it, that it is working to keep you running at your best.  We just need to stop working against it.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"January 5th, 2020","path":"/the-problem-with-weight-loss","title":"The Problem With Weight Loss","topic":"Intentional Living","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.5034965034965035,"src":"/static/0ce58248f38956d5d7b7974f91033ac8/52efb/IMG_0695.jpg","srcSet":"/static/0ce58248f38956d5d7b7974f91033ac8/f5236/IMG_0695.jpg 215w,\n/static/0ce58248f38956d5d7b7974f91033ac8/9865e/IMG_0695.jpg 430w,\n/static/0ce58248f38956d5d7b7974f91033ac8/52efb/IMG_0695.jpg 860w,\n/static/0ce58248f38956d5d7b7974f91033ac8/1ff5b/IMG_0695.jpg 1290w,\n/static/0ce58248f38956d5d7b7974f91033ac8/96dc6/IMG_0695.jpg 1720w,\n/static/0ce58248f38956d5d7b7974f91033ac8/7700f/IMG_0695.jpg 6240w","sizes":"(max-width: 860px) 100vw, 860px"}}}}},"SocialImage":{"frontmatter":{"featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","width":1200,"height":600,"src":"/static/0ce58248f38956d5d7b7974f91033ac8/51b9a/IMG_0695.jpg","srcSet":"/static/0ce58248f38956d5d7b7974f91033ac8/51b9a/IMG_0695.jpg 1x,\n/static/0ce58248f38956d5d7b7974f91033ac8/2c589/IMG_0695.jpg 1.5x,\n/static/0ce58248f38956d5d7b7974f91033ac8/c0aca/IMG_0695.jpg 2x"}}}}}},"pageContext":{}}}